cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper deals with deep learning and visual recognition tasks, which are typically covered under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). However, since the paper focuses on few-shot learning, which is a specific problem in machine learning and computer vision, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories. The use of transfer learning and semi-supervised learning also suggests that cs.AI and cs.CL are possible sub-categories. Finally, the use of deep learning models and neural networks indicates that cs.NE is also a possible sub-category.
